Package: rstudio.clipboard.path
Title: RStudio Add-ins — Working Directory from Clipboard or Active File
Version: 1.2.0
Authors@R: person("HTang", email = "tang.heng@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Two RStudio add-ins (Windows, macOS, Linux): (1) read a path from
    the system clipboard and set the working directory and Files pane (and open
    common R-related files in the editor); (2) set working directory and Files
    pane from the folder of the file open in the editor. Clipboard access uses
    the 'clipr' package; on Linux you may need xclip, xsel, or wl-clipboard.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    clipr (>= 0.4),
    rstudioapi (>= 0.13)
